        "advice": [
            {
                "type": "advice",
                "textContent": "Transdermal administration less likely to cause gastro-intestinal disturbance.\n\nTreatment should be interrupted if gastro-intestinal side-effects occur and withheld until their resolution&#8212;retitrate dose if necessary.\n\nAcetylcholinesterase inhibitors can cause unwanted dose-related cholinergic effects and should be started at a low dose and the dose increased according to response and tolerability.",
                "html": "<p>Transdermal administration less likely to cause gastro-intestinal disturbance.</p><p>Treatment should be interrupted if gastro-intestinal side-effects occur and withheld until their resolution&#8212;retitrate dose if necessary.</p><p>Acetylcholinesterase inhibitors can cause unwanted dose-related cholinergic effects and should be started at a low dose and the dose increased according to response and tolerability.</p>"
            }
        ]
    },
